<task id="051" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6">
  <metadata>
    <title>D-C-02 — `WorkspaceStateService.cs` BFF service (Redis hot + Cosmos durable, Q4 hybrid)</title>
    <status>pending</status>
    <estimated-effort>1 day</estimated-effort>
    <phase>Phase C — Tri-directional Workspace (Pillar 6a)</phase>
    <wave>C-G1 (sequential within Pillar 6a)</wave>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
    <dependencies>050 (WorkspaceTab interface)</dependencies>
    <tags>bff-api, services, cache, redis, workspace</tags>
    <rigor-level>FULL</rigor-level>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>New BFF service; multi-tier persistence; consumed by 6a endpoint + chat agent prompt builder. Architecture-defining work.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>C-G1</parallel-group>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Build `WorkspaceStateService` in `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Workspace/`
    implementing the Q4 hybrid persistence model: Redis hot tier (24h TTL) for active
    session state, Cosmos durable tier on pin-or-matter-attach. Mirrors the canonical
    workspace tab shape from task 050. Per-tenant cache key
    `workspace:{tenantId}:{sessionId}` per ADR-014. Cosmos durable rows go to either the
    existing `memory` container or a new `workspace_tabs` container (extend existing
    pattern; do NOT introduce new container if `memory` suffices). Public API: `Task&lt;
    IReadOnlyList&lt;WorkspaceTab&gt;&gt; GetTabsAsync(tenantId, sessionId, ct)`;
    `Task UpsertTabAsync(tenantId, sessionId, WorkspaceTab tab, ct)`;
    `Task PinTabAsync(tenantId, sessionId, tabId, matterId, ct)` (promotes Redis row to
    Cosmos durable); `Task CloseTabAsync(tenantId, sessionId, tabId, ct)`. Service stays
    in BFF per ADR-013 (no AI internal types injected — service is workspace-state
    plumbing, not AI capability). Register in `AnalysisServicesModule` per ADR-010 (ZERO
    new top-level Program.cs lines).
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior BFF engineer with Redis + Cosmos write-through caching experience and
    familiarity with the Spaarke BFF service-registration patterns + ADR-014 caching
    contract.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `WorkspaceStateService` registered + functional with both Redis hot and Cosmos durable
    paths. Per-tenant cache key isolation verified. Pin operation correctly promotes the
    Redis row to a Cosmos durable row tagged with matterId. Service is consumed only by
    Pillar 6a endpoint (task 052) and the chat agent factory snapshot (task 053).
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="project-spec">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-plan">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/plan.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-claude">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="root-claude">CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="bff-claude">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="bff-extensions">.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md</file>
    <file purpose="di-module">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Infrastructure/DI/AnalysisServicesModule.cs</file>
    <file purpose="workspace-tab-type">src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/types/WorkspaceTab.ts</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">AI as BFF extension; workspace-state plumbing stays in BFF. MUST NOT inject `IOpenAiClient`, `IPlaybookService`, or any AI-internal type into this service. Service is consumed by chat agent factory THROUGH the `WorkspaceStateService` interface — not vice versa.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-014">Redis hot tier cache key MUST include tenantId. Cosmos durable tier write-through pattern reused. Per-tenant isolation verified.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-010">Register inside existing `AnalysisServicesModule` (or a sibling module within the same `Infrastructure/DI/` folder). ZERO new top-level `Program.cs` lines.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">Verify publish-size delta; expect &lt;1 MB; report absolute MB + delta in task notes. Total R6 budget ≤+5 MB (NFR-02).</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-32">Redis hot 24h TTL; Cosmos durable on pin / matter-attach. Reuse `memory` container if patterns support; else add `workspace_tabs` container.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec NFR-16">Per-tenant cache key isolation — `workspace:{tenantId}:{sessionId}` MUST be enforced.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project R6 Pillar 6a binding">Service interface consumed by 6a endpoint + chat factory snapshot. Cross-pillar contract — sign-off required if signature changes mid-Phase-C.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <topic>bff/services-cache</topic>
    <files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/api/service-registration.md</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/caching/distributed-cache.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-010-di-minimalism.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-013-ai-architecture.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-014-ai-caching.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-029-bff-publish-hygiene.md</file>
      <file>.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Context Check + Rigor Declaration">
      "🔒 RIGOR LEVEL: FULL — Reason: New BFF service with multi-tier persistence; consumed by endpoint + chat factory; per-tenant isolation critical."
    </step>
    <step order="1" name="Review Progress">Read TASK-INDEX.md; confirm 050 complete; load `WorkspaceTab` interface.</step>
    <step order="2" name="Gather Resources">Read bff-extensions.md (binding placement justification) + ADR-014 caching pattern + existing Cosmos memory-container client.</step>
    <step order="3" name="Author Service Interface">Create `IWorkspaceStateService` in `Services/Workspace/` with the public API above.</step>
    <step order="4" name="Implement Service">Write `WorkspaceStateService.cs`: Redis client for hot tier (24h TTL, per-tenant key); Cosmos durable repo reused from `memory` container (or new `workspace_tabs` container — decide per existing pattern fit, document decision in task notes). Pin operation writes through.</step>
    <step order="5" name="Register in Module">Add registration to `AnalysisServicesModule` (or sibling). ZERO Program.cs changes.</step>
    <step order="6" name="Unit Tests">Add tests in `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Workspace/`: tenant isolation, TTL behavior, pin promotes to Cosmos, close removes from Redis.</step>
    <step order="7" name="Publish-Size Verification">Run `dotnet publish -c Release src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/ -o deploy/api-publish/`; measure compressed size; record absolute MB + delta vs prior baseline in task notes. Confirm against NFR-02 ≤+5 MB total R6 budget.</step>
    <step order="9.5" name="Quality Gates (FULL)">Run code-review skill; run adr-check skill — verify ADR-010, ADR-013, ADR-014, ADR-029 compliance. Verify NO HIGH-severity CVE via `dotnet list package --vulnerable --include-transitive`.</step>
    <step order="10" name="Document + Complete">TASK-INDEX 051 🔲→✅; current-task → 052; placement-justification noted per bff-extensions.md.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="dotnet">Build + test + publish + vulnerable-package check</tool>
    <tool name="git">Stage + commit</tool>
  </tools>

